    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-29T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">638.5131/142: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gordon</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-29T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 29, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. My despatches 453 of March 24, and 465 of April 7.<note n="61"
                        xml:id="d567fn61">Neither printed.</note> The Foreign Minister informed me
                    today that exchange of notes<note n="62" xml:id="d567fn62">Signed April 28,
                        1937; for text, see France, <hi rend="italic">Journal Ofllciel</hi>, May 15,
                        1937, p. 5293.</note> effecting <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> pending
                    consummation of Franco-Haitian commercial treaty negotiations had just been
                    signed. The <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi> gives Haiti a quota of
                    approximately 37,000 sacks of coffee to be shipped from here between now and
                    September 1; the French get straight minimum tariff treatment and there is no
                    mention of an <hi rend="italic">avenant</hi> or of specific tariff reductions
                    for additional non-specialty articles.</p>
                <p>Amplifying despatch by air mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gordon</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
